How to run
Download zip unzip
open folder in vscode
open the terminal in vs code

run the following codes one at a time
npm install nodemon
npm run server

let that run and open another terminal 
run the following codes one at a time:
cd frontend
npm install vite
npm run dev

open your browser of choice but it looks better in chrome
go to http://localhost:3000


////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
Make frontend and backend folders

Terminal Commands:
cd frontend
npm create vite@latest
> React
> JavaScript
npm i
npm run dev
cd backend
cd ..
npm init -y

make server.js in backend

Terminal Commands: (install packages)
npm install express dotenv cookie-parser bcryptjs mongoose socket.io jsonwebtoken

express to initialize and express server
dotenv to  read enviornmental variables under dotenv file
cookie-parser to parse cookies
bcryptjs to hash passwords
mongoose to connect database and interact with it
socket.io to have real time communication
jsonwebtoken to create tokens

Terminal Commands: 
npm install nodemon --save-dev
(allows the browser to update in the background)

